<item>
            <title>[CXF-3889] OOM when uploading files greater than 2GB</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-3889</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The totalLength field in org.apache.cxf.io.CachedOutputStream is declared as a int field, so when a file greater than 2GB is uploaded for a PUT operation, OOM is thrown.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When the file size is over 2GB the condition &apos;totalLength &amp;lt; limit&apos; becomes true when it should not.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; public void writeCacheTo(StringBuilder out, String charsetName, int limit) throws IOException {&lt;br/&gt;
294        flush();&lt;br/&gt;
295        if (totalLength &amp;lt; limit&lt;br/&gt;
296            || limit == -1) &lt;/p&gt;
{
297            writeCacheTo(out);
298            return;
299        }</description>
